modules.description: This module processes and manipulates byte strings using a set of low-level operations such as concatenation, slicing, and in-place modification. It directly works with the `bytes` type, enabling efficient handling of binary data and string-like sequences. Concrete use cases include parsing network protocols, constructing binary file formats, and optimizing memory-intensive string operations.

This module provides functions to iterate over and consume binary data from a bytestring, including reading individual bits, bytes, UTF-8 sequences, and fixed-size values. It supports parsing and validation tasks such as extracting binary-encoded integers, verifying byte patterns, and decoding strings in-place. Concrete use cases include binary protocol parsing, file format decoding, and network packet inspection.

This module provides functions to efficiently build byte strings by appending data in various forms, including raw strings, bits, integers, and UTF-8 encoded text, with optional size constraints. It works with a mutable transient buffer type `t` and produces a finalized `bytestring` upon completion. Concrete use cases include constructing binary protocols, serializing data structures, and generating network packets.

This module implements efficient creation, manipulation, and conversion of byte strings, supporting operations such as concatenation, slicing, and conversion to and from strings, iovecs, and transient buffers. It works with the abstract type `t` and a `view` type exposing offset, length, and raw data. Concrete use cases include binary protocol parsing, network packet construction, and in-place UTF-8 and integer encoding/decoding.
